      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The main danger is from blowing snow. The snowpack stability is reduced, especially on slopes and in ravines, where the snow thickness is greater due to snow drifts.\n\nLocally, weak layers in the snowpack deeper in the snowpack may be a problem. These weak layers are more prevalent in the axis above the forest. In particular, a medium-sized avalanche can be triggered by a large load exceeding the load-bearing capacity of these layers.",
